derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: via Old French from Latin dominant- 'ruling, governing', from the verb dominari (see dominate)

entry.tran: 占支配（或统治）地位的;占优势的;显著的
entry.def: Someone or something that is dominant is more powerful, successful, influential, or noticeable than other people or things.

example.ex: ...a change which would maintain his party's dominant position in Scotland...
example.tran: 将使他的政党在苏格兰继续占据支配地位的变化

example.ex: She was a dominant figure in the French film industry.
example.tran: 她在法国电影界是个举足轻重的人物。

entry.def: A dominant gene is one that produces a particular characteristic, whether a person has only one of these genes from one parent, or two genes, one from each parent.

example.ex: Because it is carried by a dominant gene, an affected individual can expect about half of his or her children to inherit the illness.
example.tran: 因为它是由显性基因携带，所以感染者的孩子会有约50％的可能性遗传该疾病。
